Dependencies:
* node.js (http://www.nodejs.org)
* npm (curl http://npmjs.org/  ##  curl http://npmjs.org/install.sh | sh)
* jslint (npm install jslint || modded version daethorian)
* pyflakes (easy_install pyflakes)
* pytest (easy_install pytest)
* rope (easy_install rope)
* dircolors (port install coreutils)
* vim (latest and greatest with python support)

The no-bullshit approach:
Download and install node.js (also installs ntp): http://www.nodejs.org
cd ~ && npm install jslint
sudo easy_install pyflakes pytest rope
sudo port install coreutils +with_default_names vim +python27

After this. you need to setup everything
* cd ~ && git clone https://github.com/daethorian/config.git
* cd ~/config && git submodule init && git submodule update
* cd zsh && git submodule init && git submodule update && cd ~/config
* cd vim && git submodule init && git submodule update && cd ~/config
* zsh install.sh -l n1ck3 vim zsh tmux

